1
00:00:02,136 --> 00:00:04,272
("Vehicle" by
Ides of March playing)

2
00:00:15,416 --> 00:00:19,653
* Hey, well, I'm the friendly
stranger in the black sedan *

3
00:00:19,687 --> 00:00:21,389
* Won't you hop inside my car?

4
00:00:21,422 --> 00:00:23,557
* I got pictures, got candy,
I'm a lovable man *

5
00:00:23,591 --> 00:00:25,626
* And I can take you
to the nearest star *

6
00:00:25,659 --> 00:00:28,362
* I'm your vehicle, baby

7
00:00:28,396 --> 00:00:31,132
* I'll take you anywhere
you wanna go *

8
00:00:31,165 --> 00:00:33,134
* I'm your vehicle, woman

9
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:35,669
* By now I'm sure you know

10
00:00:35,703 --> 00:00:37,138
* That I love ya
* Love ya *

11
00:00:37,171 --> 00:00:38,272
* I need ya
* Need ya *

12
00:00:38,306 --> 00:00:40,841
* I want you,
got to have you, child *

13
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:42,210
* Great God in heaven

14
00:00:42,243 --> 00:00:45,513
* You know I love you...

15
00:00:47,181 --> 00:00:49,217
What, have I mussed
my suit again?

16
00:00:49,250 --> 00:00:51,085
It's impossible
to keep clean, this thing.

17
00:00:51,119 --> 00:00:53,321
You have wings.

18
00:00:54,188 --> 00:00:55,723
Ah. Right, yes, forgot.

19
00:00:55,756 --> 00:00:58,826
Bit of a conversation-stopper
for you humans, isn't it?

20
00:00:58,859 --> 00:01:00,761
(sighs)

21
00:01:00,794 --> 00:01:02,196
There we go. That better?

22
00:01:02,230 --> 00:01:04,198
Ah. (chuckles)

23
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:06,600
You take care.

24
00:01:06,634 --> 00:01:08,769
All right.

25
00:01:08,802 --> 00:01:10,171
Nice suit.

26
00:01:10,204 --> 00:01:12,173
Oh, well, thank you very much.

27
00:01:12,206 --> 00:01:13,307
My grandpa had one just like it.

28
00:01:13,341 --> 00:01:15,743
Grandfather? But...
Mm-hmm.

29
00:01:15,776 --> 00:01:18,512
This was the height of fashion
last time I visited.

30
00:01:18,546 --> 00:01:20,448
Hmm. You here for business
or pleasure?

31
00:01:20,481 --> 00:01:21,649
Oh, pleasure.

32
00:01:21,682 --> 00:01:23,184
Always pleasure.

33
00:01:23,217 --> 00:01:26,120
Oh, then you came
to the right place.

34
00:01:26,154 --> 00:01:28,889
* White brother...

35
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,458
*

36
00:01:30,491 --> 00:01:32,092
(women laughing)

37
00:01:43,837 --> 00:01:47,175
ALL (chanting): Off! Off! Off!
Off! Off! Off! Off!

38
00:01:47,208 --> 00:01:48,609
(chuckles):
Mm!

39
00:01:50,944 --> 00:01:52,780
(groans)

40
00:01:52,813 --> 00:01:53,781
How can someone

41
00:01:53,814 --> 00:01:54,915
who can literally
control time

42
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:58,252
have such atrocious timing?

43
00:01:58,286 --> 00:02:00,821
Toying with
humans again, I see.

44
00:02:00,854 --> 00:02:04,192
Oh, these poor creatures.

45
00:02:04,225 --> 00:02:05,859
They know not what they do.

46
00:02:05,893 --> 00:02:06,960
I beg to differ.

47
00:02:06,994 --> 00:02:09,663
Everyone here is well aware
that they're doing me.

48
00:02:09,697 --> 00:02:11,299
Enough foolishness.

49
00:02:11,332 --> 00:02:13,534
It's time for me
to take you back to Hell.

50
00:02:13,567 --> 00:02:14,702
As always.

51
00:02:14,735 --> 00:02:18,672
Correction: allow you
to take me back, as always.

52
00:02:18,706 --> 00:02:19,740
Please.

53
00:02:19,773 --> 00:02:22,776
Everyone knows I'm the strongest
of God's children.

54
00:02:22,810 --> 00:02:25,246
Uh, not everybody.

55
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:27,281
I mean, you've never fought me,
have you, huh?

56
00:02:27,315 --> 00:02:28,449
Care to give it a try?

57
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:30,184
You know damn well
that celestial beings

58
00:02:30,218 --> 00:02:32,253
aren't allowed to
interact here on Earth.

59
00:02:32,286 --> 00:02:33,721
Now, let's go.
(sighs)

60
00:02:33,754 --> 00:02:36,890
It's dangerous for humanity
to be exposed to divinity.

61
00:02:36,924 --> 00:02:38,526
Well, I wouldn't
sit on that couch--

62
00:02:38,559 --> 00:02:40,494
left a lot of divinity there.

63
00:02:40,528 --> 00:02:43,231
Enough!

64
00:02:43,264 --> 00:02:45,199
Now, you can either
deal with me,

65
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:47,768
or you can deal with Father.

66
00:02:50,738 --> 00:02:52,806
Yeah.

67
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,575
That's what I thought.

68
00:02:54,608 --> 00:02:56,210
Very well.

69
00:02:56,244 --> 00:02:58,212
Well, at least allow me
to say my good-byes.

70
00:02:58,246 --> 00:03:01,249
I mean, that's just manners,
isn't it? Not that you'd know.

71
00:03:01,282 --> 00:03:02,783
Ten minutes.

72
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:08,289
(whispers):
Right.

73
00:03:15,396 --> 00:03:16,830
Nice dress.

74
00:03:16,864 --> 00:03:17,931
It's a robe.

75
00:03:17,965 --> 00:03:19,267
You wear it well.

76
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:23,504
Humans.

77
00:03:25,406 --> 00:03:27,441
(three gunshots)

78
00:03:31,979 --> 00:03:35,283
What are you looking at?
Nothing.

79
00:03:35,816 --> 00:03:37,285
I'm just...

80
00:03:48,796 --> 00:03:49,763
(gasps)

81
00:03:49,797 --> 00:03:51,732
(panting)

82
00:03:54,668 --> 00:03:57,271
My necklace.

83
00:03:57,305 --> 00:03:59,407
*

84
00:04:06,614 --> 00:04:11,285
LUCIFER: And this little demon
went, "Wee, wee, wee, wee, wee,"

85
00:04:11,319 --> 00:04:13,621
all into the valley of sin.

86
00:04:13,654 --> 00:04:14,455
(laughs)

87
00:04:14,488 --> 00:04:15,923
There's been a change
of plans, Luci.

88
00:04:15,956 --> 00:04:17,658
Oh, G...

89
00:04:19,927 --> 00:04:22,530
Oh. Not what I expected,
but, uh,

90
00:04:22,563 --> 00:04:24,298
all right, fine, have fun.

91
00:04:24,332 --> 00:04:25,866
Just go in the other room.

92
00:04:27,735 --> 00:04:29,637
Or not.

93
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:31,639
Sorry, are you going somewhere?

94
00:04:31,672 --> 00:04:36,477
Uh... listen,
I have an errand to run.

95
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:38,312
Why are there holes
in your dress?

96
00:04:38,346 --> 00:04:39,447
It's a robe.

97
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,280
Oh, I apologize.

98
00:04:40,314 --> 00:04:42,015
Why are there holes
in your dress?

99
00:04:42,049 --> 00:04:45,719
Look, I don't trust you to see
yourself back to Hell, okay?

100
00:04:45,753 --> 00:04:48,389
So I want you to stay here
for a few hours,

101
00:04:48,422 --> 00:04:49,390
and then we'll go.

102
00:04:49,423 --> 00:04:51,592
Oh. More time in L.A.

103
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:53,627
Lucky me. (chuckles)

104
00:04:58,832 --> 00:05:00,934
You see, I respect
the rule of human law,

105
00:05:00,968 --> 00:05:02,703
which is why
I'm seeking your assistance

106
00:05:02,736 --> 00:05:04,605
in a matter
of utmost importance.

107
00:05:04,638 --> 00:05:06,474
A robbery has occurred.

108
00:05:11,679 --> 00:05:13,080
Okay.

109
00:05:13,113 --> 00:05:14,482
What was stolen?

110
00:05:14,515 --> 00:05:16,484
My necklace.

111
00:05:16,517 --> 00:05:18,386
The estimated value?

112
00:05:18,419 --> 00:05:20,754
It's hard to say,
really, uh...

113
00:05:20,788 --> 00:05:24,658
It's not of this world,
so there's that.

114
00:05:26,494 --> 00:05:27,895
Priceless beyond measure.

115
00:05:27,928 --> 00:05:30,030
I'll just put down $40.

116
00:05:30,063 --> 00:05:31,532
Where did the incident occur?

117
00:05:31,565 --> 00:05:34,101
In an alleyway south of
"Cahunana" and Franklin.

118
00:05:34,134 --> 00:05:35,102
Cahuenga?

119
00:05:35,135 --> 00:05:36,737
"Cahunana" and Franklin.

120
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:39,540
Now, this thief
was armed,

121
00:05:39,573 --> 00:05:42,643
and, oh, yes, uh,
I made a rendering.

122
00:05:42,676 --> 00:05:46,780
And I do believe that this
should help you with your quest.

123
00:05:46,814 --> 00:05:48,516
Okay.

124
00:05:52,986 --> 00:05:55,122
So a jack-o'-lantern
stole your necklace?

125
00:05:55,155 --> 00:05:57,791
So you know this man?

126
00:05:57,825 --> 00:06:00,628
Where can I find
this Mr. O'Lantern?

127
00:06:02,129 --> 00:06:04,064
Did Paolucci put you up to this?

128
00:06:04,097 --> 00:06:07,034
You know it's a crime
to file a false report, right?

129
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:11,138
You think I would lie?

130
00:06:11,171 --> 00:06:13,941
What?
(phone ringing)

131
00:06:13,974 --> 00:06:15,108
Sorry, excuse me.

132
00:06:15,142 --> 00:06:16,644
Just two seconds.

133
00:06:17,578 --> 00:06:18,812
Hey, honey, what's up?

134
00:06:18,846 --> 00:06:20,581
DAN:
I'm not gonna make date night.

135
00:06:20,614 --> 00:06:21,682
Oh, that's all right.

136
00:06:21,715 --> 00:06:23,817
My mom just called,
and she has to shoot tonight,

137
00:06:23,851 --> 00:06:26,420
so she can't watch
Trixie anyhow.

138
00:06:26,454 --> 00:06:27,521
Well, I'm gonna be home
pretty late.

139
00:06:27,555 --> 00:06:28,656
You want me to pick up
some dinner?

140
00:06:28,689 --> 00:06:30,758
No, that's okay. There's stuff
for tacos in the fridge,

141
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:31,825
and we'll make it a thing.

142
00:06:31,859 --> 00:06:32,960
We'll call it "Taco Tuesday."

143
00:06:32,993 --> 00:06:33,961
Trixie will love it.

144
00:06:33,994 --> 00:06:35,629
Cool.

145
00:06:35,663 --> 00:06:36,797
So, what are you doing?

146
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:38,732
I caught a body
on Franklin and Cahuenga.

147
00:06:38,766 --> 00:06:39,567
Really?

148
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,502
That's so weird;
a guy just came in,

149
00:06:41,535 --> 00:06:42,836
reporting a mugging near there.

150
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:46,073
I wonder if it has
anything to do...

151
00:06:46,106 --> 00:06:48,609
with your homicide.

152
00:06:50,010 --> 00:06:51,078
Lucifer.

153
00:06:51,111 --> 00:06:52,513
(groans)

154
00:06:52,546 --> 00:06:55,182
If only angels came
with a snooze button.

155
00:06:55,215 --> 00:06:56,950
What? What is
it, Brother?

156
00:06:56,984 --> 00:06:59,820
A human shot me
and stole my necklace.

157
00:06:59,853 --> 00:07:04,024
Well, so much for not exposing
humanity to our divinity.

158
00:07:04,057 --> 00:07:06,894
Which is why I need
to get it back, all right?

159
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:08,596
Oh.

160
00:07:08,629 --> 00:07:10,698
Now, I tried to utilize
human law enforcement,

161
00:07:10,731 --> 00:07:13,100
but it failed, so...

162
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:15,603
(sighs)

163
00:07:15,636 --> 00:07:18,672
...I need
your help, Luci.

164
00:07:18,706 --> 00:07:21,542
(chuckles)
Oh, do you now?

165
00:07:23,544 --> 00:07:27,014
Well, you've always
been crafty...

166
00:07:27,047 --> 00:07:28,516
smart...

167
00:07:28,549 --> 00:07:30,618
Craftier,
smarter than you.

168
00:07:30,651 --> 00:07:32,486
Yes, and
more handsome.

169
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,787
Go on.

170
00:07:33,821 --> 00:07:36,790
And because you've spent
more time with humanity,

171
00:07:36,824 --> 00:07:38,759
you may understand them
better than I do.

172
00:07:38,792 --> 00:07:42,195
Well, most of that time, I was
naked, but true nonetheless.

173
00:07:42,229 --> 00:07:44,965
Luci, are you gonna
help me or not?

174
00:07:44,998 --> 00:07:46,534
Hmm.

175
00:07:46,567 --> 00:07:47,701
Okay.

176
00:07:47,735 --> 00:07:51,104
But you have
to follow me.

177
00:07:51,138 --> 00:07:53,106
*

178
00:08:20,768 --> 00:08:22,736
(siren whooping)

179
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:24,738
(indistinct
police radio chatter)

180
00:08:25,639 --> 00:08:28,108
Detective Espinoza.

181
00:08:28,141 --> 00:08:30,544
Excuse me.

182
00:08:30,578 --> 00:08:31,745
Officer Decker.

183
00:08:31,779 --> 00:08:32,746
Hi.
Hi.

184
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:34,648
How's it going?

185
00:08:34,682 --> 00:08:37,985
Dan, not at work, remember?

186
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:38,952
Sorry.

187
00:08:38,986 --> 00:08:39,987
Hey, remember the, uh, robbery

188
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:42,122
I told you about,
happened around the corner?

189
00:08:42,155 --> 00:08:42,790
Yeah.

190
00:08:42,823 --> 00:08:45,258
Um, so I searched the area,

191
00:08:45,292 --> 00:08:46,727
and I found this.

192
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:48,829
It looks like a key fob.

193
00:08:48,862 --> 00:08:51,264
I don't know to what, but it
looks like there's blood on it,

194
00:08:51,298 --> 00:08:54,001
and... do you think this could
be connected to your homicide?

195
00:08:54,034 --> 00:08:55,803
Could be,
but even if it is,

196
00:08:55,836 --> 00:08:58,005
all signs point to
a random attacker.

197
00:08:58,038 --> 00:09:00,107
A serial mugger
on a spree.
Hmm.

198
00:09:00,140 --> 00:09:04,011
Looks like my guy resisted
and ended up dead.

199
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:05,679
That's the guy
that got mugged?
Yeah.

200
00:09:05,713 --> 00:09:07,180
He's built like a tank.
Yeah.

201
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:09,883
And so is the guy that
reported the robbery.

202
00:09:09,917 --> 00:09:11,852
They're the last two guys
that I'd try to mug.
Yeah.

203
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:15,723
Yeah, well, a gun can be
a pretty great equalizer.

204
00:09:16,857 --> 00:09:18,859
I don't think
this was random, Dan.

205
00:09:18,892 --> 00:09:21,161
Okay, I'll look
into it, but...

206
00:09:21,194 --> 00:09:23,631
only when I'm done;
it's gonna be a while.

207
00:09:23,664 --> 00:09:25,065
Okay, why don't I
get a jump on it?

208
00:09:25,098 --> 00:09:26,366
No.

209
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:29,336
Dan, you said to make detective,

210
00:09:29,369 --> 00:09:30,904
I have to
show initiative, right?

211
00:09:30,938 --> 00:09:33,841
Right. Right.
Mm-hmm.

212
00:09:33,874 --> 00:09:37,377
Let me know what you hear,
Officer Decker.

213
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:39,747
(piano playing jazz music)

214
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:41,248
Oh, lovely.

215
00:09:43,216 --> 00:09:45,719
(chuckles)
Amazing.

216
00:09:45,753 --> 00:09:47,855
Does no one work in this town?

217
00:09:47,888 --> 00:09:50,090
Is this where thieves come
to spend their spoils

218
00:09:50,123 --> 00:09:51,692
on wine and women?

219
00:09:51,725 --> 00:09:53,026
Something like that, yeah.

220
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:57,297
Oh. Brother, listen to that.

221
00:09:57,330 --> 00:09:59,700
Oh.

222
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:02,736
I haven't heard music
like that since...

223
00:10:02,770 --> 00:10:04,071
well, since
the Silver City.

224
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:06,073
What, there's
no music in Hell?

225
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:08,909
Only for torture,
and usually out of tune.

226
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:11,879
Lately, we've been playing music
by this chap named Bieber.

227
00:10:11,912 --> 00:10:13,046
Gosh, you should
hear the screams.

228
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:16,116
Why don't you go and, um,
grab us a couple of drinks,

229
00:10:16,149 --> 00:10:18,285
and I'll do some
reconnaissance.

230
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:22,122
*

231
00:10:26,259 --> 00:10:27,327
Do you take requests?

232
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,129
What do you want to hear?

233
00:10:29,162 --> 00:10:31,665
Uh, myself.

234
00:10:31,699 --> 00:10:33,300
Thank you.

235
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:37,170
(sighs)

236
00:10:37,204 --> 00:10:39,039
(playing David Bowie's
"Changes")

237
00:10:44,945 --> 00:10:47,815
You didn't come here
to find this thief, did you?

238
00:10:47,848 --> 00:10:50,150
You're just trying to stall
your return to Hell.

239
00:10:50,183 --> 00:10:52,686
Oh, I really hoped to get
a few more drinks in

240
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,887
before you worked that one out.

241
00:10:53,921 --> 00:10:55,956
Luci, this isn't some game.

242
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:58,225
Now, how many times
do I have to tell you?

243
00:10:58,258 --> 00:11:00,027
Humanity should not
be exposed to...

244
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:01,895
It's just a necklace,
for crying out loud.

245
00:11:01,929 --> 00:11:03,230
You promised me
that you would help.

246
00:11:03,263 --> 00:11:06,099
And I am by distracting you
from the painful reality

247
00:11:06,133 --> 00:11:08,235
that you're never
going to find it.

248
00:11:10,170 --> 00:11:12,773
(resumes playing "Changes")

249
00:11:12,806 --> 00:11:16,009
TV REPORTER:
...found earlier today
near Cahuenga and Franklin.

250
00:11:16,043 --> 00:11:18,712
The police have identified
the murder victim

251
00:11:18,746 --> 00:11:20,914
as MMA fighter Aiden Scott.

252
00:11:20,948 --> 00:11:24,084
Scott's body was found
this morning,

253
00:11:24,117 --> 00:11:26,186
the victim of
an apparent shooting.

254
00:11:26,219 --> 00:11:27,788
Luci, look.

255
00:11:27,821 --> 00:11:29,122
His family has been notified.

256
00:11:29,156 --> 00:11:32,092
Born in Lancaster, California,

257
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:34,427
Aiden Scott moved
to Los Angeles...

258
00:11:34,461 --> 00:11:35,729
What?

259
00:11:35,763 --> 00:11:37,731
I know this man.

260
00:11:37,765 --> 00:11:40,934
Uh, the runner,
right before the theft.

261
00:11:40,968 --> 00:11:43,236
What, you think he had
something to do with it?

262
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:44,437
