00:22:42,028 --> 00:22:44,964
* Try to believe
though the going gets rough *

524
00:22:44,997 --> 00:22:46,599
* That you got to hang tough
to make it... *

525
00:22:46,633 --> 00:22:47,767
Go!

526
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:48,868
* You're the best around

527
00:22:48,901 --> 00:22:50,102
(imitates clucking)

528
00:22:50,136 --> 00:22:52,472
* Nothing's gonna
ever keep you down... *

529
00:22:52,505 --> 00:22:54,040
LUCIFER:
Uh, uh-uh! No.

530
00:22:54,073 --> 00:22:55,742
No cheating.

531
00:22:55,775 --> 00:22:57,009
* Nothing's gonna
ever keep you down *

532
00:22:57,043 --> 00:22:58,478
* You're the best...

533
00:22:58,511 --> 00:22:59,412
Eh.

534
00:22:59,446 --> 00:23:04,851
* Nothing's gonna
ever keep you down *

535
00:23:04,884 --> 00:23:07,019
* Down...

536
00:23:07,053 --> 00:23:09,021
(straining)

537
00:23:11,057 --> 00:23:12,992
Very good.

538
00:23:15,562 --> 00:23:17,163
Finally.

539
00:23:17,196 --> 00:23:19,165
Lovely. Yes. Yes.

540
00:23:19,198 --> 00:23:20,433
Yes.

541
00:23:20,467 --> 00:23:21,434
There we go.

542
00:23:24,804 --> 00:23:26,473
(Lucifer laughs)

543
00:23:26,506 --> 00:23:28,007
Oh, Brother.

544
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:30,443
Your fighter
looks good.

545
00:23:30,477 --> 00:23:31,911
Well, I certainly hope so,

546
00:23:31,944 --> 00:23:34,581
'cause I'm ready
to make some cash.

547
00:23:34,614 --> 00:23:37,049
Which is all
I really care about.

548
00:23:37,083 --> 00:23:39,586
Cold hard cash.

549
00:23:39,619 --> 00:23:42,054
Win or lose?

550
00:23:42,088 --> 00:23:44,824
Whatever it takes.

551
00:23:46,626 --> 00:23:48,461
So he'd take a fall?

552
00:23:50,730 --> 00:23:51,964
For the right price.

553
00:23:51,998 --> 00:23:55,468
Rumor has it that Aiden Scott
was offered a hell of a deal,

554
00:23:55,502 --> 00:23:57,804
so we want the same.

555
00:23:57,837 --> 00:24:00,206
Well, that someone is me.

556
00:24:00,239 --> 00:24:02,108
Lovely.

557
00:24:10,249 --> 00:24:12,552
CHLOE:
Dan.

558
00:24:12,585 --> 00:24:13,820
Hey, what's up?

559
00:24:13,853 --> 00:24:15,822
Hey.
Who's that?

560
00:24:15,855 --> 00:24:17,957
One of Tio Sorrento's thugs.

561
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:20,159
The, uh, fight promoter
you were telling me about.

562
00:24:20,192 --> 00:24:22,729
Yeah. Who was seen
arguing with Aiden Scott

563
00:24:22,762 --> 00:24:24,096
just before he was killed.

564
00:24:24,130 --> 00:24:26,165
Tats here has
multiple warrants out,

565
00:24:26,198 --> 00:24:28,067
and after a little squeeze,
I found out

566
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:30,102
that Tio fixes fights
for the Sarkisians.

567
00:24:30,136 --> 00:24:31,938
As in the Sarkisian
crime family?

568
00:24:31,971 --> 00:24:33,973
Yeah, so what if Tio tried
to fix Aiden's fight,

569
00:24:34,006 --> 00:24:35,842
and he refused,
and he killed him for it?

570
00:24:35,875 --> 00:24:38,778
Well, I'd say that's
a pretty interesting theory.

571
00:24:38,811 --> 00:24:40,246
I sense there's an "and" coming.

572
00:24:40,279 --> 00:24:41,948
And I'd like to talk
to Tio's lawyer,

573
00:24:41,981 --> 00:24:44,517
see if I can maneuver a deal.
Not a good idea.

574
00:24:44,551 --> 00:24:47,654
Why?
'Cause you don't have any
actual proof yet, Chloe.

575
00:24:47,687 --> 00:24:48,655
All right? If
you're wrong,

576
00:24:48,688 --> 00:24:50,089
you get nothing
and Tio knows we're onto him.

577
00:24:50,122 --> 00:24:52,725
Dan, I'm right. I can feel it.

578
00:24:52,759 --> 00:24:53,893
Chloe, we'll
look into Tio.

579
00:24:53,926 --> 00:24:56,128
But right now, you
got to be patient.

580
00:25:03,636 --> 00:25:05,772
(chuckles softly)

581
00:25:07,607 --> 00:25:08,575
(door closes)

582
00:25:08,608 --> 00:25:09,609
Oh.

583
00:25:09,642 --> 00:25:10,710
(clears throat)

584
00:25:10,743 --> 00:25:12,545
So, uh...

585
00:25:12,579 --> 00:25:13,479
has he got your necklace?

586
00:25:13,512 --> 00:25:15,247
He claims to not know
it's whereabouts.

587
00:25:15,281 --> 00:25:18,084
(school bell rings over TV,
TV clicks off)

588
00:25:18,117 --> 00:25:20,887
I suppose it's time
to torture him.

589
00:25:21,921 --> 00:25:24,023
So, you're up.
(scoffs)

590
00:25:24,056 --> 00:25:26,092
Look, just because
I am the King of Hell

591
00:25:26,125 --> 00:25:28,595
doesn't mean I actually
do the torturing.

592
00:25:28,628 --> 00:25:29,996
I'm more of
a delegator.

593
00:25:30,029 --> 00:25:32,999
But I assumed this
was going to happen,

594
00:25:33,032 --> 00:25:35,702
so I popped back down
while you were in there

595
00:25:35,735 --> 00:25:38,605
and brought
up the best.

596
00:25:38,638 --> 00:25:39,806
You remember Mazikeen.

597
00:25:55,387 --> 00:25:56,956
Hello, human.

598
00:25:56,989 --> 00:25:58,658
(grunts)

599
00:25:58,691 --> 00:26:00,026
Where am I?

600
00:26:00,059 --> 00:26:01,227
Who are you?

601
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:03,963
I'm a demon.

602
00:26:03,996 --> 00:26:05,965
And I've risen from
the bowels of Hell

603
00:26:05,998 --> 00:26:08,034
to torture you.
I already told
that other guy

604
00:26:08,067 --> 00:26:10,603
I don't know nothing
about Aiden Scott.

605
00:26:10,637 --> 00:26:12,872
(laughs)

606
00:26:14,140 --> 00:26:18,645
That "other guy" wouldn't
know a flanged mace

607
00:26:18,678 --> 00:26:20,680
from this...

608
00:26:21,881 --> 00:26:23,015
...stabbing object.

609
00:26:26,285 --> 00:26:29,722
I'm here for the truth.

610
00:26:29,756 --> 00:26:31,323
You don't have to do this.

611
00:26:31,357 --> 00:26:32,692
No.

612
00:26:32,725 --> 00:26:34,627
I get to do this.

613
00:26:34,661 --> 00:26:35,895
(grunts)

614
00:26:35,928 --> 00:26:37,363
Asphyxiation?
(shouts)

615
00:26:37,396 --> 00:26:39,365
Electrocution?

616
00:26:39,398 --> 00:26:41,400
There are so many ways

617
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:43,670
I could hurt you.

618
00:26:44,303 --> 00:26:46,238
I just can't decide.

619
00:26:48,975 --> 00:26:50,943
Wow.

620
00:26:50,977 --> 00:26:52,044
I'm on fire,

621
00:26:52,078 --> 00:26:53,913
aren't you?

622
00:26:53,946 --> 00:26:55,381
No.

623
00:26:55,414 --> 00:26:58,150
I thought Hell was hot.

624
00:26:58,184 --> 00:27:00,687
(exhales, growls)

625
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:03,890
Well, that human
didn't kill anybody.

626
00:27:03,923 --> 00:27:07,426
(Tio crying in distance)

627
00:27:07,459 --> 00:27:10,429
And he doesn't know where your
stupid necklace is, either.

628
00:27:10,462 --> 00:27:12,799
Also a bit of a crier, it seems.

629
00:27:12,832 --> 00:27:14,300
I hope you didn't
go too hard, Maze.

630
00:27:14,333 --> 00:27:15,968
He's not in Hell yet.

631
00:27:16,002 --> 00:27:17,169
Oh, no.

632
00:27:17,203 --> 00:27:19,305
Those are tears of joy.

633
00:27:19,338 --> 00:27:21,207
Oh, so he's a masochist.

634
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:21,908
(chuckles)

635
00:27:21,941 --> 00:27:23,309
They can be
quite tricky.

636
00:27:23,342 --> 00:27:24,310
What did you use

637
00:27:24,343 --> 00:27:25,311
to inflict the pain?

638
00:27:25,344 --> 00:27:27,046
Nothing.
Hmm?

639
00:27:27,079 --> 00:27:30,750
In Hell, I have to use their own
guilt against them as torture.

640
00:27:30,783 --> 00:27:32,218
The method is
chosen for them,

641
00:27:32,251 --> 00:27:33,452
but here, Lucifer...

642
00:27:33,485 --> 00:27:34,887
(stammers)

643
00:27:34,921 --> 00:27:36,322
...infinite possibilities.

644
00:27:36,355 --> 00:27:37,924
I got so excited,

645
00:27:37,957 --> 00:27:39,726
I just had sex with him.

646
00:27:39,759 --> 00:27:40,659
(groans)

647
00:27:40,693 --> 00:27:42,428
(laughs):
And then he wouldn't shut up.

648
00:27:42,461 --> 00:27:44,864
(laughs)
Enough.

649
00:27:46,398 --> 00:27:49,201
That man tried to bribe me into
throwing a fight, all right?

650
00:27:49,235 --> 00:27:51,437
Now, he practically admitted
doing the same with Aiden Scott,

651
00:27:51,470 --> 00:27:52,939
so he must be lying to you.

652
00:27:52,972 --> 00:27:55,975
Nobody lies to me.

653
00:27:56,008 --> 00:27:57,476
The human said
he wanted to fix

654
00:27:57,509 --> 00:28:01,080
the dead one's fight,
but someone beat him to it.

655
00:28:01,113 --> 00:28:04,083
Said someone placed
a huge anonymous bet.

656
00:28:04,116 --> 00:28:05,885
Half a million dollars
on Aiden Scott losing.

657
00:28:05,918 --> 00:28:06,986
AMENADIEL:
Whoever placed that bet

658
00:28:07,019 --> 00:28:09,822
probably killed Aiden Scott
and stole my necklace.

659
00:28:09,856 --> 00:28:12,391
Tio doesn't know
who that is, either.

660
00:28:12,424 --> 00:28:15,762
Said they only communicated
anonymously...

661
00:28:15,795 --> 00:28:17,830
...through burner phones
and dead drops.

662
00:28:17,864 --> 00:28:20,466
So Tio has no idea
who this man is,

663
00:28:20,499 --> 00:28:22,869
and no way of finding out.

664
00:28:22,902 --> 00:28:25,738
Which basically means
your so-called torture

665
00:28:25,772 --> 00:28:26,873
has been useless.

666
00:28:30,943 --> 00:28:32,511
You want to go, bird boy?

667
00:28:32,544 --> 00:28:34,213
Ooh, now this is
getting interesting.

668
00:28:34,246 --> 00:28:36,082
Luci, we still need
to find this thief.

669
00:28:36,115 --> 00:28:37,016
(sighs)

670
00:28:37,049 --> 00:28:39,351
And you're not gonna...

671
00:28:39,385 --> 00:28:41,120
Very well.

672
00:28:41,153 --> 00:28:44,023
Whoever stole your necklace
tried to gamble on a sure thing.

673
00:28:44,056 --> 00:28:48,861
So, maybe we could persuade
our thief to gamble on another.

674
00:28:48,895 --> 00:28:50,529
So if we convince
this killer thief

675
00:28:50,562 --> 00:28:52,164
to bet on my fight instead,

676
00:28:52,198 --> 00:28:54,166
and I take the fall
I promise to take,

677
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:56,435
then we wait wherever the money
is supposed to be dropped off,

678
00:28:56,468 --> 00:28:57,837
and then we see who shows up.

679
00:28:57,870 --> 00:28:59,338
You are cleverer than you look.

680
00:28:59,371 --> 00:29:03,175
Maze, do you think you can
persuade Tio to arrange that?

681
00:29:05,477 --> 00:29:07,213
Where should I begin?

682
00:29:10,082 --> 00:29:12,985
Excuse me-- oh, no, no.
I'm good. Charlotte Richards.

683
00:29:13,019 --> 00:29:14,987
Hi. I'm here regarding
your client Tio Sorrento.

684
00:29:15,021 --> 00:29:16,488
ETIENNE: I'm sorry,
Ms. Richards, she just...

685
00:29:16,522 --> 00:29:18,290
Oh, it's fine, Etienne.

686
00:29:18,324 --> 00:29:20,960
I always have time
for law enforcement.

687
00:29:20,993 --> 00:29:24,063
You are law
enforcement, yes?

688
00:29:24,096 --> 00:29:26,065
Yes, I, um...
I'm Officer Decker,

689
00:29:26,098 --> 00:29:28,067
and I'm here to help Tio.

690
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:30,870
And what makes you think
that I need your help

691
00:29:30,903 --> 00:29:33,439
representing my client? Hmm?

692
00:29:33,472 --> 00:29:36,943
Uh, well, because we know he
works for the Sarkisian family.

693
00:29:36,976 --> 00:29:38,845
Mm-hmm.
And he's also implicated

694
00:29:38,878 --> 00:29:40,880
in the murder
of Aiden Scott.

695
00:29:40,913 --> 00:29:43,082
So if he agrees
to speak with us,

696
00:29:43,115 --> 00:29:44,817
we'll go easier on him.

697
00:29:44,851 --> 00:29:47,386
Have you ever heard of
something called "leverage,"

698
00:29:47,419 --> 00:29:48,454
Officer Decker?

699
00:29:50,122 --> 00:29:52,524
If not, let me help you.

700
00:29:52,558 --> 00:29:55,094
It's like pressure or influence,

701
00:29:55,127 --> 00:29:58,397
and it's something
that you currently can't apply,

702
00:29:58,430 --> 00:30:00,599
because none of what you
said actually resembles

703
00:30:00,632 --> 00:30:02,368
proof of a crime.

704
00:30:02,401 --> 00:30:03,502
Why do you say that?

705
00:30:03,535 --> 00:30:06,438
Because when you're out there
writing traffic tickets,

706
00:30:06,472 --> 00:30:09,976
I'm representing families
like the Lings and the Sokolovs.

707
00:30:10,009 --> 00:30:11,143
Actual killers.

708
00:30:12,311 --> 00:30:14,546
Alleged, anyway.

709
00:30:14,580 --> 00:30:18,851
So it's going to take
a lot more than spunk--

710
00:30:18,885 --> 00:30:23,489
especially rookie spunk--
and a prayer to intimidate me.

711
00:30:26,458 --> 00:30:28,961
You represent
the Sokolov family?

712
00:30:28,995 --> 00:30:30,930
And you also represent

713
00:30:30,963 --> 00:30:32,531
Tio and the Sarkisians.

714
00:30:32,564 --> 00:30:34,934
So, I-I thought
the Sarkisians

715
00:30:34,967 --> 00:30:36,268
and the Sokolovs were at war

716
00:30:36,302 --> 00:30:38,637
over their bookmaking
operations.

717
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:40,372
I wonder how they'd feel
if they knew

718
00:30:40,406 --> 00:30:43,475
that their lawyer
was double-dipping.

719
00:30:43,509 --> 00:30:46,145
(chuckles): You know,
I'm-I'm new at this, so...

720
00:30:46,178 --> 00:30:49,015
I don't know what the term is
for what you're doing,

721
00:30:49,048 --> 00:30:51,918
but I think
it's called "leverage."

722
00:30:56,088 --> 00:30:58,057
Please have a seat, Officer.

723
00:30:58,090 --> 00:31:00,392
Aw, thank you.

724
00:31:06,432 --> 00:31:09,035
I didn't expect you
to be so happy

725
00:31:09,068 --> 00:31:10,970
to lose your first
fight ever, Brother.

726
00:31:11,003 --> 00:31:12,071
And to a human, no less.

727
00:31:12,104 --> 00:31:14,373
Nice try, Luci, but we both
know this doesn't count.

728
00:31:14,406 --> 00:31:16,308
Ah.
Not to mention the fact

729
00:31:16,342 --> 00:31:18,310
that no mere mortal could
ever stand a chance

730
00:31:18,344 --> 00:31:19,946
against the full power
of my God-given...

731
00:31:19,979 --> 00:31:20,913
Forget it.
I regret mentioning it.

732
00:31:20,947 --> 00:31:24,483
(music thumping, crowd cheering
in distance)

733
00:31:24,516 --> 00:31:26,285
(bell dings)

734
00:31:26,318 --> 00:31:27,954
Looks like you might be
up soon, Brother.

735
00:31:27,987 --> 00:31:29,956
Luci, thanks.

736
00:31:29,989 --> 00:31:32,491
What?
Thanks for your help.

737
00:31:32,524 --> 00:31:35,427
I mean, I... will admit
that I was a bit skeptical

738
00:31:35,461 --> 00:31:38,330
of your plan, but this
might actually work.

739
00:31:38,364 --> 00:31:39,698
Yes, of course
it'll work, Brother.

740
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:41,067
That's why you asked me,
remember?

741
00:31:41,100 --> 00:31:43,002
Someone crafty, smart...

742
00:31:43,035 --> 00:31:45,004
And evil. (laughs)

743
00:31:46,672 --> 00:31:47,706
Evil?

744
00:31:47,739 --> 00:31:49,942
Well, if you want to find
a deplorable criminal,

745
00:31:49,976 --> 00:31:52,511
you just ask a-- well,
you know what I mean, Luci.

746
00:31:52,544 --> 00:31:53,645
Come on.

747
00:31:53,679 --> 00:31:55,714
You are the Devil, after all.

748
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:58,050
*

749
00:32:13,299 --> 00:32:15,634
ANNOUNCER (over P.A.):
Ladies and gentlemen,

750
00:32:15,667 --> 00:32:17,636
we have a scratch on the card.

751
00:32:17,669 --> 00:32:23,976
Please welcome
a new fighter to the cage:

752
00:32:24,010 --> 00:32:26,412
Lucifer...

753
00:32:26,445 --> 00:32:29,115
Morningstar!

754
00:32:29,148 --> 00:32:31,183
(crowd cheering)

755
00:32:31,217 --> 00:32:33,285
You wanted the Devil.

756
00:32:33,319 --> 00:32:36,222
Well, you got him.

757
00:32:39,725 --> 00:32:40,993
(bell dings)
Where's the human fighter?

758
00:32:41,027 --> 00:32:43,129
Off to join
the Renaissance fair,

759
00:32:43,162 --> 00:32:44,730
whatever that is.

760
00:32:44,763 --> 00:32:46,432
Apparently, he
loves the mandolin.

761
00:32:46,465 --> 00:32:48,134
So that leaves you

762
00:32:48,167 --> 00:32:49,301
with big bad me.

763
00:32:49,335 --> 00:32:50,769
Why are you doing this, Lucifer?

764
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:53,072
(chuckles):
Well, who better than the Devil

765
00:32:53,105 --> 00:32:56,242
to help you do something
so wickedly dishonest

766
00:32:56,275 --> 00:32:58,277
as to throw a fight?

767
00:32:58,310 --> 00:32:59,311
(both grunt)

768
00:32:59,345 --> 00:33:01,547
You're welcome, by the way.
This is pointless!

769
00:33:01,580 --> 00:33:03,749
Well, we're finally answering
the age-old question:

770
00:33:03,782 --> 00:33:06,052
"Who'd win in a fight,
you or me?"

771
00:33:06,085 --> 00:33:08,387
This doesn't count!

772
00:33:08,420 --> 00:33:10,456
So be it, Brother.

773
00:33:10,489 --> 00:33:12,458
So be it.

774
00:33:12,491 --> 00:33:14,160
*

775
00:33:14,193 --> 00:33:15,561
(both grunting)

776
00:33:22,068 --> 00:33:24,603
I'll make sure I tell
everyone in Heaven and Hell

777
00:33:24,636 --> 00:33:27,373
how the undefeated
warrior lost

778
00:33:27,406 --> 00:33:30,142
to his loser, evil,
little brother. (chuckles)

779
00:33:30,176 --> 00:33:33,412
Oh, I guess you're not so tough
after all, are you, eh?

780
00:33:33,445 --> 00:33:35,647
Daddy's boy.

781
00:33:39,685 --> 00:33:41,420
(yells)

782
00:33:49,461 --> 00:33:51,697
(crowd cheers)

783
00:33:51,730 --> 00:33:53,332
See?

784
00:33:53,365 --> 00:33:55,134
You're just as bad
as me, Brother.

785
00:33:56,668 --> 00:33:58,537
Pride is your sin, too.

786
00:34:00,339 --> 00:34:01,373
(Lucifer yells)

787
00:34:01,407 --> 00:34:03,775
